  "prompt": "How do you remember which continents are located in the northern hemisphere?",
  "response": "Remembering which continents are located in the northern hemisphere can be made easier with mnemonics or associations. Here\u2019s a simple way to recall them:\n\n1. **North America** - The name itself gives it away (\"North\").\n2. **Europe** - Located entirely in the northern hemisphere.\n3. **Asia** - The vast majority of Asia is in the northern hemisphere, except for parts of Southeast Asia.\n4. **Africa** - The northern part of Africa is above the equator, though the continent spans both hemispheres.\n5. **South America** - Only the northern part of South America is in the northern hemisphere.\n\n### Mnemonic:\nYou can use the acronym **\"NEASA\"** to remember the continents in the northern hemisphere:\n- **N**orth America  \n- **E**urope  \n- **A**sia  \n- **S**outh America  \n- **A**frica  \n\nAlternatively, visualize the Earth and note that these continents are mostly or entirely above the equator. Practice and repetition will also help solidify your knowledge!",
